Package com.irurueta.navigation.inertial.navigators

Class ECIInertialNavigator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.irurueta.navigation.inertial.navigators.ECIInertialNavigator
  • public class ECIInertialNavigator
extends java.lang.Object
    Runs precision ECI-frame inertial navigation equations. This implementation is based on the equations defined in "Principles of GNSS, Inertial, and Multisensor Integrated Navigation Systems, Second Edition" and on the companion software available at: https://github.com/ymjdz/MATLAB-Codes/blob/master/Nav_equations_ECI.m

                     double angularRateX,
                     double angularRateY,
                     double angularRateZ,
                     ECIFrame result)
              throws InertialNavigatorException,
                     InvalidSourceAndDestinationFrameTypeException
        Runs precision ECI-frame inertial navigation equations.
        Parameters:
        timeInterval - time interval between epochs expressed in seconds (s).
        oldX - previous cartesian x-coordinate position of body frame with respect ECI frame, resolved along ECI-frame axes and expressed in meters (m).
        oldY - previous cartesian y-coordinate position of body frame with respect ECI frame, resolved along ECI-frame axes and expressed in meters (m).
        oldZ - previous cartesian z-coordinate position of body frame with respect ECI frame, resolved along ECI-frame axes and expressed in meters (m).
        oldC - previous body-to-ECI-frame coordinate transformation.
        oldVx - previous velocity x-coordinate of body frame with respect ECI frame, resolved along ECI-frame axes and expressed in meters per second (m/s).
        oldVy - previous velocity y-coordinate of body frame with respect ECI frame, resolved along ECI-frame axes and expressed in meters per second (m/s).
        oldVz - previous velocity z-coordinate of body frame with respect ECI frame, resolved along ECI-frame axes and expressed in meters per second (m/s).
        fx - specific force x-coordinate of body frame with respect ECI frame, resolved along body-frame axes, averaged over time interval and expressed in meters per squared second (m/s^2).
        fy - specific force y-coordinate of body frame with respect ECI frame, resolved along body-frame axes, averaged over time interval and expressed in meters per squared second (m/s^2).
        fz - specific force z-coordinate of body frame with respect ECI frame, resolved along body-frame axes, averaged over time interval and expressed in meters per squared second (m/s^2).
        angularRateX - angular rate x-coordinate of body frame with respect ECI frame, resolved along body-frame axes, averaged over time interval and expressed in radians per second (rad/s).
        angularRateY - angular rate y-coordinate of body frame with respect ECI frame, resolved along body-frame axes, averaged over time interval and expressed in radians per second (rad/s).
        angularRateZ - angular rate z-coordinate of body frame with respect ECI frame, resolved along body-frame axes, averaged over time interval and expressed in radians per second (rad/s).
        result - instance where new estimated ECI frame containing new body position, velocity and coordinate transformation matrix will be stored.
        Throws:
        InertialNavigatorException - if navigation fails due to numerical instabilities.
        InvalidSourceAndDestinationFrameTypeException - if source or destination frame types of previous body-to-ECI-frame coordinate transformation matrix are invalid.
